%S A396062 110,11155,1125000,131250000,970312500000
%N A396062 Define the level of a number in A395720 as the largest integer m such that repeated application of the inner operation can be performed m times, with each intermediate value remaining in A395720. Let a(n) be the smallest kangaroo number in A395720 of level n.
%C A396062 a(n) > 10^60 for n >= 6 if it exists. - _David A. Corneth_, May 15 2026
%H A396062 Michael S. Branicky, <a href="/A396062/a396062.py.txt">Python program for OEIS A396062</a>
%e A396062 a(4) = 131250000, because: 131250000 = 3125000*42, 3125000 = 12500*250, 12500 = 250*50 and 250 = 5*50.
